I"o<p>chili relleno recipe
pasilla peppers w/stem
 tomato sauce - delmonte or heintz 
yellow or white onion
montery jack cheese</p>
<ul>
  <li>A.P.F.</li>
  <li>
    <p>one egg per pasilla</p>

    <p>Roast peppers over open flame</p>

    <p>to blackened in parts - do not over cook</p>

    <p>place pepper in zip lock bag to steam - then peel off skin of pepper.  cut slot in pepper and remove seeds.  stuff with jack cheese and dust with A.P.F.
      separate egg whites and yokes - beat wite to peaks and then incorporate egg yokes back into mixture.  dip relleno into egg white and fry in oil.<br />
  cover holes with mixture.  golden brown then turn. remove to plate.	Slice onion and saute.  Add tomatoe sauce - heat to simmer. then add 1/2 can chicken stock.<br />
  heat to simer.  salt to taist <br />
  Add chili relleno to sauce. heat and serve.</p>

    <p>Spanish Rice</p>
    <ul>
      <li>one cup rice</li>
      <li>one cup h20</li>
      <li>one cup chx stock</li>
      <li>one tomato</li>
      <li>one quarter oinion</li>
      <li>1/4 cup Oil</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Blend tomato in 1/2 cup water.  add oil into pan - heat and add onion and rice -  toast rice to golden brown.  add tomatoe mixture - boil to cook tomato.  add last 1/2 cup water and 1 cup chx stock.  Bring to a boil then set to simmer.  cover and cook until moister absorbed into rice</p>
  </li>
</ul>

